You are creating `PrintWriter` like this 

    PrintWriter writer  = new PrintWriter(System.out);

The variable is named `writer`, but you use it like this:

    printr.print(arr[i]);

Using `printr` variable which doesn&#39;t exist. Do simply:
    
    writer.print(arr[i]);

Also, you need `PrintStream` acts as a buffer, so you will have to flush it&#39;s contents so that they are written to the output stream.

